    <string name="setup_battery_dialog_title">Background running (RingerGuard only)</string>
    <string name="setup_battery_dialog_body">This setting applies only to RingerGuard — not your whole phone and not other apps.\n\nRingerGuard is very lightweight. It checks your ringer every few minutes and should have almost no noticeable effect on battery life.\n\nWithout this, Samsung and Android may stop RingerGuard from working, and you could miss calls.\n\nOn the next screen, scroll to RingerGuard and turn it ON.</string>

    <string name="setup_exact_alarm_dialog_title">Scheduled checks (RingerGuard only)</string>
    <string name="setup_exact_alarm_dialog_body">This lets RingerGuard run its periodic ringer checks on time, even when battery saver is on.\n\nIt applies only to RingerGuard. Allow it on the next screen.</string>

    <string name="setup_dnd_dialog_title">Optional: Do Not Disturb access</string>
    <string name="setup_dnd_dialog_body">You do not need this for RingerGuard to work.\n\nOnly enable this if you want RingerGuard to turn off Do Not Disturb when it restores your ringer — for example, if your phone was silenced by DND after a meeting.\n\nIf you manage DND yourself, tap Skip.</string>

    <string name="welcome_title">Welcome to RingerGuard</string>
    <string name="welcome_body">RingerGuard keeps your ringer on unless you explicitly silence it. After a grace period, it restores volume automatically.</string>

    <string name="phone_disclosure_title">Why RingerGuard needs phone access</string>
    <string name="phone_disclosure_body">RingerGuard detects when you dismiss an incoming call (without answering) so it can start a grace period before restoring your ringer.\n\nRingerGuard does not access your phone number, call history, or contacts. This permission is optional.</string>
